──────────────────────

When running code, DockerService:

1. Detects runtime from repository:
   ├─ Python: requirements.txt, setup.py, pyproject.toml
   ├─ Node.js: package.json
   ├─ Java: pom.xml
   ├─ Go: go.mod
   └─ Ruby: Gemfile

2. Selects appropriate image

3. Creates container:
   docker run -d \
     --name ide_exec_<session_id> \
     --cpus=2 \
     --memory=512m \
     -v /tmp/repos/<repo_id>:/workspace \
     -w /workspace \
     -e DATABASE_URL=... (if testing DB) \
     -e NODE_ENV=test \
     <image_name> \
     /bin/bash -c "<command>"

4. Streams output to frontend via WebSocket

5. Waits for exit code

6. Cleans up container:
   docker stop ide_exec_<session_id>
   docker rm ide_exec_<session_id>

Resource limits:
├─ CPU: 2 cores max
├─ Memory: 512MB max
├─ Timeout: 5 minutes (configurable)
├─ Disk: 1GB per container
└─ Network: Isolated (no internet access)
