## 🔒 Security Considerations

```
1. CONTAINER ISOLATION
   ├─ Read-only file systems where possible
   ├─ Resource limits (CPU, memory, disk)
   ├─ Network isolation (no internet access)
   └─ User namespacing (non-root user inside)

2. CODE EXECUTION
   ├─ Timeout on all commands (5 minutes default)
   ├─ Kill zombie processes
   ├─ Clean up containers after execution
   └─ No access to host system

3. FILE ACCESS
   ├─ Only within repository directory
   ├─ No symlink escapes
   ├─ Validate file paths
   └─ Prevent directory traversal attacks

4. CREDENTIALS
   ├─ GitHub token stored in secure env vars
   ├─ Never expose in logs
   ├─ Rotate tokens regularly
   └─ Audit all git operations

5. AUDIT LOGGING
   ├─ Log all file changes
   ├─ Log all commands executed
   ├─ Log all git operations
   ├─ Log all validation results
   └─ Log all PR creations
```

